<P>
USC UPSETS OREGON IN FINAL HOME GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
USC concluded its home season with a 66-61 upset victory over Oregon in a 
Pacific 10 women's basketball game Sunday night at USC. 
</P>
<P>
Oregon earlier this season defeated USC by 22 at Eugene, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
Senior Tammy Hammond led USC (7-16, 5-9) with 14 points and nine rebounds. 
Oregon is 16-9, 8-6. 
</P>
<P>
The Trojans conclude their season with road games at Washington, Washington 
State and UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA 74, Oregon State 55 -- Sandra VanEmbricqs had 19 points and a career-high 
18 rebounds to lead the Bruin women (16-9, 11-4) over Oregon State (5-22, 1-13) 
at UCLA. 
