<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIT-AND-RUN DRIVER KILLS 2 PEDESTRIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two pedestrians were killed by a hit-and-run driver as they crossed Burbank 
Boulevard in Tarzana Sunday afternoon, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Arnold Feldman, 61, and a 37-year-old Tarzana woman whose name was not released 
pending notification of relatives, were struck by a white car as they crossed 
the street in the 18600 block of Burbank Boulevard, said Los Angeles Police 
Sgt. Joe Cross. 
</P>
<P>
Cross said the two people were crossing mid-block when the car struck them. 
Both were taken to Northridge Hospital Medical Center, where they were 
pronounced dead. 
</P>
<P>
One witness said the car, which has not been identified, did not pause after 
the accident and headed west on Burbank Boulevard, Cross said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
