<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOWNHOUSE FIRE KILLS WOMAN, 88 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 88-year-old woman died Saturday night in a fire at her Thousand Oaks 
townhouse, Ventura County fire officials reported. 
</P>
<P>
The woman lived alone and was not identified pending notification of her 
family. 
</P>
<P>
She was found dead in the living room in the 1000 block of Glenbridge Circle, 
where the fire was reported at 10:15 p.m., fire dispatcher Annie Ironside said. 
Authorities said the woman had been smoking and they believe that was the cause 
of the fire. 
</P>
<P>
The fire started in the living room and spread to the townhouse next door 
through a common attic, causing $125,000 worth of damage to each unit, Ironside 
said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no injuries to the next-door neighbors. It took about 55 
firefighters 35 minutes to control the blaze. 
</P>
</TEXT>
