<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Screening Shows Work of Latino Students: UCLA Film School will be showcasing 
the work of seven Latino student film makers tonight at 7:30 p.m. in Melnitz 
Hall in what the school is calling the first university Chicano film screening 
of student work. Five films and three videos will be screened, three of the 
films having won awards. Community leaders will be on hand as will film makers 
Moctesuma Esparza ("Milagro Beanfield War") and Gregory Nava ("El Norte"), both 
UCLA graduates. BETH KLEID 
</P>
