<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rocky Loses to Museum: It looks as if Rocky Balboa has lost his bout with the 
Philadelphia Museum of Art. The 8-foot, 6-inch statue of the fictional South 
Philadelphia palooka is scheduled to leave its spot atop the art museum's steps 
today for its former home at the Spectrum arena, a museum spokeswoman said 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The statue of Rocky was moved from the Spectrum for the filming of "Rocky V." 
The film's producers had agreed to put the statue back when they were through, 
but Sylvester Stallone and Rocky fans tried to persuade the museum to keep it 
on the spot made famous in the original "Rocky." But art museum officials say 
it's out of place in front of the Greco-Roman building. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
