<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The president of soccer's governing body wants rule changes to accommodate 
television for the 1994 World Cup, the first to be played in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
Joao Havelange, president of the International Federation of Association 
Football, was quoted Sunday in Rio de Janeiro as saying games should be divided 
into four 25-minute quarters instead of two 45-minute halves to allow more 
commercials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
