</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Boeing to Help Those Laid Off: The Boeing Co. for the first time will offer to 
help find jobs for the 2,500 employees that it expects to lay off this spring. 
Boeing will open two out-placement centers early next month to prepare its 
laid-off workers to re-enter the job market, the company said. Last month 
Boeing announced that it will trim 5,000 jobs from its payroll this year, most 
from its Everett, Wash., plant. 
</P>
