<P>
Gas Prices Edge Down: Motorists are paying a half-cent less for gasoline than 
they were two weeks ago, said industry analyst Trilby Lundberg. The average 
price of all grades of gasoline at retail stations fell 0.52 cents per gallon 
between Feb. 9 and Feb. 23, to $1.1221 per gallon, according to Lundberg. The 
decrease followed a decline of 0.60 cents per gallon recorded during the 
previous two-week reporting period. 
