78 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
BRITAIN; 
</P>
<P>
POLL SHOWS THATCHER PARTY FAR BEHIND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Britain's opposition Labor Party has a 17-point lead over the ruling 
Conservatives, its highest ranking in Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher's decade 
in power, a poll found. Thatcher's political fortunes have been declining amid 
economic stagnation and Britain's isolated stance in international forums on 
issues such as South Africa and European union. The survey gave Labor 51%, the 
Conservatives 34%, the centrist Liberal Democrats 5% and other parties 10%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
