<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BREA; 
</P>
<P>
CAR STRIKES MAN ON ROAD, KILLING HIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A La Habra man was killed late Saturday night when he was struck by a car as he 
tried to run across Lambert Road near Berry Street here, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, whose name was being withheld until relatives could be notified, 
died at the scene of the 10:47 p.m. accident, they said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the car was not arrested or cited. 
</P>
<P>
Lt. Tom Christian of the Police Department said the man ran across Lambert and 
into the path of the car, which was traveling west. 
</P>
<P>
The driver was unable to swerve to avoid him, witnesses told police. 
</P>
<P>
An investigation is continuing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
