<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAZZ ALL-STARS SCHEDULED FOR SERIES AT CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pat Metheny, Branford Marsalis and other critically acclaimed names in jazz 
highlight a three-concert contemporary-jazz series announced today by the 
Orange County Performing Arts Center. 
</P>
<P>
The Modern Jazz Quartet, a long-running group that treats jazz with classical 
refinement, and the Kronos Quartet, a classical string quartet whose music 
bends eclectically in the direction of pop, rock and jazz, will open the series 
on April 22. 
</P>
<P>
A June 15 concert features a quartet of jazz all-stars: drummer Jack 
DeJohnette, pianist Herbie Hancock, bassist Dave Holland and guitarist Pat 
Metheny. 
</P>
<P>
The series ends Nov. 29 with a performance by the Branford Marsalis Quartet, 
led by the young saxophonist whose career has swung between the be-bop 
tradition and rock explorations with Sting. 
</P>
<P>
Subscription tickets for the entire series go on sale March 18. Information: 
(714) 556-ARTS, Ext. 240. MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Branford Marsalis 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
