<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
TREVINO'S DAUGHTER WINS, TOO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SARASOTA, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lee Trevino's putting has given a big boost to his daughter's driving. 
</P>
<P>
Trevino capped another lucrative weekend on the Senior PGA Tour by rolling in a 
15-foot birdie putt Sunday on the final hole of the Chrysler Cup to win a new 
LeBaron convertible. 
</P>
<P>
The car went to the player with the lowest final round. Trevino tied Don Bies 
for the honor with a 3-under-par 69 and won the contest because he birdied No. 
18, the tiebreaker hole. 
</P>
<P>
Easy come, easy go. The hottest player in golf said he'll give away the car. 
</P>
<P>
"I've got all the Toyotas in the world," said Trevino, who does commercials for 
the Japanese auto maker. "I've got a daughter, Lesley -- 23 years old, and 
she's never asked me for a thing. I think my daughter needs this car real bad." 
</P>
</TEXT>
